{"tid":2170284,"cid":5,"subCid":10,"title":"德國初步研究：81% 無感染者，已能對新冠病毒產生T-免疫細胞反應","createTime":"2020-08-23T07:15:55.000Z","updateTime":"2020-08-23T10:22:22.000Z","uid":270206,"like":8,"dislike":2,"uniUserReply":15,"replies":[{"pid":"b480825539ad7927349f2bb429568295bc056517","tid":2170284,"uid":270206,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2020-08-23T07:15:55.000Z","msg":"德國初步研究：81% 無感染者，已能對新冠病毒產生T-免疫細胞反應<br />\n<br />\n德國科學家團隊研究本來的目的，是找出能引發身體T-細胞免反應的新冠病毒的抗原決定簇 (epitopes, 即是病毒表面的蛋白質標記)，用以研發抗病毒藥物及疫苗之用。他們取180名 新冠病康復者、185名無染病者的血液樣本作對照研究。血液中的T-細胞反應，有針對新冠病毒 (specific)，也有廣泛應對其他冠狀病毒 (cross-reactive)。有趣的發現是， 沒染病者的81%的血液樣本，也會對新冠病毒的細胞原決定簇產生 T-細胞免的免疫反應。<br />\n<br />\n測試樣本中，染病者血液樣本的T-細胞反應，明顯較無染病者強烈。而T-細胞反應較為廣泛的樣本者，其新冠病的病微會較輕復。<br />\n<br />\n引起新冠病或武漢肺炎 (COVID-19) 的為 新冠病毒 (SARS-CoV-2) 。現已知共七種人類冠狀病毒，其中四種可引致輕微的感冒： OC43、HKU1、229E、NL63，另有三種較嚴重的：MERS-CoV、SARS-CoV、SARS-CoV-2， 分別引發中東呼吸症候群、沙士 (非典型肺炎)、新冠病(武肺)。<br />\n<br />\n今次這個德國研究發現，大部份人對新冠病已有一定程度的免疫力。猜想，或者本地學者該研究，香港、臺灣曾於二零零三年受沙士重創，所以今次新冠病毒對兩地人的直接健康影響極微？  <br />\n<br />\n另外，如果沒染病的81% 人已對新冠病能有免疫反應，那新冠疫苗的價值又何在呢？ (科學界對疫苗的期望，也只是75%有效，50-60% 有效率已要接受。)<br />\n<br />\n:<br />\n:<br />\n:<br />\n詳見：<br />\n德國研究：<br />\n1. SARS-CoV-2 T-cell epitopes dene heterologous and COVID-19-induced T-cell recognition<br />\n<a href=\"https://www.researchsquare.com/article/rs-35331/v1\" data-sr-url=\"https://r.lihkg.com/link?u=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.researchsquare.com%2Farticle%2Frs-35331%2Fv1&d=MZ%2BcikgbnzcLbT%2Fpq7%2BWTFNDr8uFEZb%2F0ofPPvrEBCw%3D&h=7e19c52c\" data-auto-link target=\"_blank\">https://www.researchsquare.com/article/rs-35331/v1</a><br />\n<br />\n美國 Science 學報上相關研究：<br />\n2. Selective and cross-reactive SARS-CoV-2 T cell epitopes in unexposed humans. 4 Aug 2020.<br />\nDOI: 10.1126/science.abd3871<br />\n<br />\nAbstrac\bt: Many unknowns exist about human immune responses to the SARS-CoV-2 virus. SARS-CoV-2 reactive CD4+ T cells have been reported in unexposed individuals, suggesting pre-existing cross-reactive T cell memory in 20-50% of people. However, the source of those T cells has been speculative. Using human blood samples derived before the SARS-CoV-2 virus was discovered in 2019, we mapped 142 T cell epitopes across the SARS-CoV-2 genome to facilitate precise interrogation of the SARS-CoV-2-specific CD4+ T cell repertoire. We demonstrate a range of pre-existing memory CD4+ T cells that are cross-reactive with comparable affinity to SARS-CoV-2 and the common cold coronaviruses HCoV-OC43, HCoV-229E, HCoV-NL63, or HCoV-HKU1. Thus, variegated T cell memory to coronaviruses that cause the common cold may underlie at least some of the extensive heterogeneity observed in COVID-19 disease.<br />\n<img src=\"https://na.cx/i/EpfbTzT.jpg\" data-thumbnail-src=\"https://i.lih.kg/thumbnail?u=https%3A%2F%2Fna.cx%2Fi%2FEpfbTzT.jpg&h=e1992594&s={SIZE}\" />"},{"pid":"d687eaffd038f81d824407352276fa7a4713cdc4","tid":2170284,"uid":81273,"like":3,"dislike":3,"score":0,"citedBy":1,"replyTime":"2020-08-23T07:17:30.000Z","msg":"陳雲<img src=\"/assets/faces/big/adore.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},{"pid":"f42ad0898eed0a03beafa272aecf8845ec86fb87","tid":2170284,"uid":270206,"like":1,"dislike":7,"score":-6,"quote":{"pid":"d687eaffd038f81d824407352276fa7a4713cdc4","tid":2170284,"uid":81273,"like":3,"dislike":3,"score":0,"citedBy":1,"replyTime":"2020-08-23T07:17:30.000Z","msg":"陳雲<img src=\"/assets/faces/big/adore.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2020-08-23T07:18:35.000Z","msg":"德國熱狗<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/sosad.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /><br />\n本來我信美國同德國個研究<br />\n但陳雲<img src=\"/assets/faces/pig/whip.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /><br />\n我地唱反調<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/agree.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},{"pid":"565fb42532d1bfeaaa707dc680b2db3de16c7f5c","tid":2170284,"uid":19217,"like":2,"dislike":2,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2020-08-23T07:24:25.000Z","msg":"國師又中<img src=\"/assets/faces/pig/sowhat.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /><img src=\"/assets/faces/pig/sowhat.gif\" class=\"hkgmo